article.headline: Harvey helps Portland State top Northern Colorado 82-72 in OT
article.description: — Bobby Harvey made six 3-pointers and scored 26 to help Portland State rally for an 82-72 overtime victory over Northern Colorado on Thursday night.
article.linkText: Harvey helps Portland State top Northern Colorado 82-72 in OT

article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- — Bobby Harvey made six 3-pointers and scored 26 to help Portland State rally for an 82-72 overtime victory over Northern Colorado on Thursday night. Harvey made 9 of 17 shots, adding eight rebounds for the Vikings (15-11, 6-7 Big Sky Conference). KJ Allen totaled 15 points and eight rebounds. Ismail Habib pitched in with 14 points, five rebounds and five assists. Dejour Reaves scored 27 points off the bench to lead the Bears (15-10, 8-4). He sank 12 of 25 shots with three 3-pointers and grabbed five rebounds. Saint Thomas finished with 14 points, 14 rebounds and six of his team's 11 turnovers. Allen scored the first four points at the free-throw line and Portland State never trailed in the extra period. ——- Get poll alerts and updates on AP Top 25 basketball throughout the season.
